Fill and boil your #kettle{} with @water to use for the pasta.

Preheat your #oven{} to 200 degrees.

Chop the @broccoli{1/2}(chopped into florets) into florets (like small trees).

Pop the broccoli onto a #baking tray{} and drizzle with a little @oil{}, @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Roast on the top shelf of the oven until crispy and tender,
~{12-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @echalion shallot{1/2}(peeled and
thinly sliced). Finely chop the @sun-dried tomatoes{15}(finely chopped).

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Roughly
chop the @flat leaf parsley{1}(roughly chopped).

Chop the @British turkey steaks{2}(chopped into 2cm pieces) into 2cm pieces.

> IMPORTANT: Remember to wash your hands after handling raw meat.

== Pasta ==

Fill a large #saucepan{} with the @boiling water{100%ml} from the kettle.

Bring back to the boil, then add the @wholewheat penne{148g} and a good pinch of
@salt{pinch}.

Boil for ~{10%minutes} then drain in a #colander{}.

== Sauce ==

While the pasta cooks, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{}
over medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the turkey, sun-dried tomatoes and onion.

Cook, turning occasionally, until the turkey has browned all over and the onion
is soft, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Add the garlic to the frying pan and cook for ~{1%minute}. Add the
@chicken stock powder{1/2} and water (see ingredients for amount).

Stir to dissolve the stock powder. Bring to the boil then reduce the heat and
simmer until the turkey is cooked and the sauce has slightly reduced, stirring
occasionally, ~{5-8%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The turkey is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle!

== To Serve ==

Stir the half the parsley and @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g} into the
sauce.

Add the pasta to the frying pan and gently mix to coat the pasta well.

Season to taste with lots of @pepper{} and @salt{} (if necessary).

Serve in #bowls{} with the broccoli on top and finish with a sprinkle of
remaining cheese and parsley.

Drizzle with @balsamic vinegar{12%ml}. Enjoy!